:"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Machine Learning</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://web.stanford.edu/class/cs20si/index.html\">CS20si</a> <strong>Tensorflow for Deep Learning Research</strong> <em>Stanford University</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\">\n<ul>\n<li>This course will cover the fundamentals and contemporary usage of the Tensorflow library for deep learning research. We aim to help students understand the graphical computational model of Tensorflow, explore the functions it has to offer, and learn how to build and structure models best suited for a deep learning project. Through the course, students will use Tensorflow to build models of different complexity, from simple linear/logistic regression to convolutional neural network and recurrent neural networks with LSTM to solve tasks such as word embeddings, translation, optical character recognition. Students will also learn best practices to structure a model and manage research experiments.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/chiphuyen/tf-stanford-tutorials\">Assignments</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/chiphuyen/tf-stanford-tutorials\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":10185,\"repo\":\"chiphuyen/tf-stanford-tutorials\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> available on Github.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-12T07:24:41.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cryengine.com\">CRYENGINE</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/CRYTEK-CRYENGINE/CRYENGINE\">:octocat:</a> - But can it run Crysis?  Some auxillary tools use Qt.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-12T03:58:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.malwarebytes.com\">Malwarebytes</a> - Your Windows desktop's personal bodyguard.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-12T03:58:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://desktop.telegram.org\">Telegram Desktop</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/telegramdesktop/tdesktop\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/telegramdesktop/tdesktop\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">20k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":19986,\"repo\":\"telegramdesktop/tdesktop\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Secure your conversations so well, you'll raise the blood pressure of potential eavesdroppers.  The desktop client uses Qt and is open source.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-12T03:58:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"ht